  "subject": "Fixing issues with handling PolicyTypes having multiple versions",
  "commit_message": "Fixing issues with handling PolicyTypes having multiple versions\n\nIn ToscaServiceTemplate class, policyType/dataType is a Map<String, T>,\nand this key String in the Map is taking in only the name, not version.\nThis can lead to issues when new versions are created.\n\nIn this fix, version is appended to the name and put as key. We could\nalso change the String to PfConceptKey so that name and version are\nconsidered.\n\nChange-Id: I0050c978ba6b29510fd4269c52641655c82b48f4\nIssue-ID: POLICY-1402\nSigned-off-by: a.sreekumar <ajith.sreekumar@est.tech>\n",
